Governor Ifeanyi Okowa, has commiserated with the Governor of Anambra State, Willie Obiano,Anambra people, particularly Onitsha residents over the tragic fire incident that gutted parts of the commercial city.

















It was recalled that a tanker laden with petroleum product on Wednesday reportedly spilled its content on the road at Upper Iweka Road in Onitsha which led to the inferno that resulted in the death of some people and destruction of many buildings, including business premises in the town.














The Governor had said that the images he saw of theÂ  fire incident were heartbreaking.













Okowa extended his sympathy to people who suffered varying degrees of losses in the unfortunate incident.








			
